entity.name: Updates on COVID-19 in Australia
entity.description: This page is a timeline of Tweets with information and advice from the prime minister, state and federal governments, health authorities and other trusted sources from around Australia. For more, visit https://www.health.gov.au/.

text:
14 new cases of #COVID19 were diagnosed in the 24 hours to 8pm last night, bringing the total number of cases in NSW to 3,303.

8 cases counted today include five who attended the Crossroads Hotel in Casula, and 3 are contacts of cases who were at the hotel. They are isolating. https://t.co/DzhfeeeAJw
